Reasoning: The paper discusses the practicability of Nash's Embedding Theorem in vision and imaging sciences, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also explores the existence of isometric embeddings of polyhedral surfaces, which could fall under the discrete geometry (cs.DG) and computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also touch upon some aspects of mathematical imaging (cs.MG), which deals with the mathematical foundations of imaging sciences.
